track_notes: Coming from south, it is a nice walk, but you have to drive a long time on this small road! There is not realy path at the end, but the trig point is not difficult to find, plenty room for antenna

This is a long way to reach the summit (14km)
Get some water if warm wx.

No evident trace on this summit, just walk and find your best way. At the end when going back you can find a trace going to Col de Segra or Col du Farguet.
Summit and activation point is heading north, but you can go and have a look on south for a nice view onto the cost.
Happy SOTA

track_title: Track for F/AM-552 from Col de Castillon
